d</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":64,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":73,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Walter Strickland was born about 1151, in Great Strickland, Westmorland, England as the son of Adam de Castlecarrock. He had at least 2 sons with Christina. He died from 1236 to 1239, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1151–between 1236 and 1239":"umbes 1151–1236 kuni 1239","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1151–1239":"1151–1239","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1176–1230":"1176–1230","1177–1246":"1177–1246","1130–1215":"1130–1215","before 1215":"enne 1215","about 1151":"umbes 1151","before 1231":"enne 1231","from 1236 to 1239":"1236 kuni 1239","1176":"1176","1154":"1154","between 1236 and 1239":"1236 kuni 1239","1230":"1230","1130":"1130","1151":"1151","1150":"1150","1228":"1228","1239":"1239","1215":"1215","123